# ⛔ RULE 1: NEVER CREATE FILES IN THE PROJECT ROOT. NO .json, .ps1, .js, .txt, .html, NOTHING.
# ⛔ RULE 2: NEVER USE CURL. This is MCP STDIO. Use native tool calls only.
# ⛔ RULE 3: ALWAYS check browser_sessions before browser_open. Reuse sessions.

# This is an MCP STDIO server (Node.js + Playwright).
# Port 1000 = dashboard only. NOT for AI tool execution.

# FILE RULES:
# - Source code → src/
# - Temp files / tests / experiments → browser_scratchpad_write tool
# - Root auto-cleans on startup. Any junk files you create WILL be deleted.

# TOOL USAGE:
# 1. browser_sessions → check existing
# 2. browser_open { url } → open/reuse
# 3. browser_analyze { sessionId } → find selectors
# 4. browser_click / browser_type / browser_fill_form → interact
# 5. browser_screenshot { sessionId, embedImage: true, saveLocal: false } → verify

# CRITICAL:
# - browser_fill_form > repeated browser_type (5x faster)
# - browser_analyze BEFORE any click/type (find valid selectors)
# - embedImage: true, saveLocal: false on screenshots (shows in chat, no disk clutter)
# - If wrapper like use_mcp_tool: pass args in nativeArgs object
# - NEVER access tools as resources (mcp://... URIs are INVALID for tools)

# Read MCP_TOOL_GUIDE.md for full tool catalog.
